==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Identism
<hw>I*den"tism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Identity</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Metaph.)</fld> <def>The doctrine taught
by <persfn>Schelling</persfn>, that matter and mind, and subject and
object, are identical in the Absolute; -- called also the
<altname>system of identity</altname> <it>or</it> <altname>doctrine of
identity</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Identity</ent>⟦br⟧
